y with chondritic\nmaterial e.g. for HD100546, while the inner disk of HD142527 show no sign of\nchondrule material. Comparison between spectra indicate a general similarity\nbetween primitive solar system materials and circumstellar dust and comets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2022 17:30:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
