\\times10^{-12}$~M$_\\odot$) compared to the total\ndust mass in the ER ($\\gtrsim10^{-5}$~M$_\\odot$) to account for the observed\n$HKs$ flux. The NIR continuum emission, however, expands slower than the more\ndiffuse 180-K dust emission that dominates in the MIR, indicating a different\nsource, and the same hot dust component cannot account for the $J$-band\nemission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 31 Dec 2022 10:29:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 May 2023 10:00:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-30"}
